WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:52.500 --> 02:54.752
Answer the phone!

02:56.462 --> 02:57.546
No answer.

02:57.629 --> 02:59.589
Keep trying -- I'm sure
he's on his way back from...

02:59.673 --> 03:01.258
Definitely on his way.

03:02.426 --> 03:04.428
Why doesn't anybody
answer the phone?!.

03:09.098 --> 03:10.766
Hello?

03:10.850 --> 03:13.227
James, you are so dead.

03:13.269 --> 03:14.103
Shit!

03:17.773 --> 03:18.691
Oh!

03:23.529 --> 03:24.779
Sorry!

03:26.489 --> 03:28.450
Excuse me -- James Clayton.

03:28.533 --> 03:30.368
Sorry I'm late.
I had a water bed emergency.

03:30.452 --> 03:31.536
Bill Rudolph, Dell.

03:31.619 --> 03:33.413
Nice to meet you.
Can I borrow your computer?

03:33.496 --> 03:35.122
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

03:35.205 --> 03:36.123
Hi, guys.

03:36.206 --> 03:38.417
-Hey.

03:40.210 --> 03:41.628
Ah...

03:41.670 --> 03:43.254
It's here somewhere.

03:43.338 --> 03:45.423
Here we go. All right.

03:48.551 --> 03:50.094
At 7:00 this morning,
sound asleep,

03:50.178 --> 03:52.096
I heard this cracking noise --
ripping wood.

03:52.138 --> 03:54.348
I figure it's part of this
logging dream I'm having,

03:54.431 --> 03:56.391
but, no, the bed
is falling through the floor.

03:56.475 --> 03:59.353
Our program uses
existing wireless technology...

03:59.436 --> 04:00.563
Which we modified,

04:00.646 --> 04:02.439
transforming it into
a completely new program.

04:02.522 --> 04:04.107
-And what do you call it?
-"Sp@rtacus."

04:04.191 --> 04:05.734
Why is that?

04:05.776 --> 04:07.110
It was named after
the revolt...

04:07.194 --> 04:09.112
Of the slaves.

04:09.196 --> 04:11.614
-Wireless Webcast.

04:11.656 --> 04:13.074
We have that.

04:13.115 --> 04:15.576
"Sp@rtacus" turns
any specified broadcast terminal

04:15.660 --> 04:17.161
into its slave.

04:17.244 --> 04:18.663
We control the program.

04:18.704 --> 04:20.245
Watch.

04:21.873 --> 04:23.583
Take a look.
Pick a screen.

04:25.627 --> 04:27.087
Hello, Bill Rudolph.

04:30.172 --> 04:33.050
Hey, who is this guy?
Somebody's hacking in.

04:33.133 --> 04:34.718
What is this?

04:43.393 --> 04:44.645
This is wonderful.

04:44.728 --> 04:46.230
Thank you.

04:46.271 --> 04:49.357
Can you, uh, put our logo
on the Sony booths?

04:49.440 --> 04:52.026
Sure...
for the right price.

04:53.653 --> 04:55.488
-We'll talk, yeah?
-Yeah.

04:55.571 --> 04:56.571
Good.

04:57.698 --> 05:01.201
# What if I don't wanna hear
the things you say? #

05:01.284 --> 05:05.080
# Where were you
when I was needy yesterday? #

05:05.122 --> 05:10.710
# You want in with me
now that it's good #

05:10.751 --> 05:13.587
# But it's too little,
too late #

05:13.629 --> 05:17.173
# Time and again,
I've asked you #

05:17.257 --> 05:18.967
# Just for some light #

05:19.009 --> 05:21.302
-Thank you.
- # To show the way #

05:21.386 --> 05:24.638
-Hey.
- # I was in total darkness #

05:24.722 --> 05:26.682
-What would you like?
- # You act like,,, #

05:26.765 --> 05:29.060
I would like
to teach you something.

05:29.227 --> 05:31.104
Okay. I'm pretty busy
right now.

05:31.187 --> 05:34.565
James, the most important
thing you need to know

05:34.648 --> 05:36.108
is that you don't know shit.

05:37.735 --> 05:39.236
What you see...

05:40.988 --> 05:42.905
...what you hear...

05:45.325 --> 05:49.162
Nothing...is...

05:49.245 --> 05:52.039
what it seems.

05:56.752 --> 05:57.669
Drink?

05:57.753 --> 05:58.920
Martini.

05:59.004 --> 06:00.464
Sure.

06:00.505 --> 06:02.590
That's how it begins, you know.

06:02.673 --> 06:05.468
Call will come in a day or two.

06:05.551 --> 06:07.261
His name is John Medica.

06:07.345 --> 06:09.889
He's head of R&D for Dell.

06:09.972 --> 06:13.350
He's gonna invite you out
for martinis.

06:13.433 --> 06:15.519
Before long,
you're gonna be working

06:15.603 --> 06:17.855
out of Advanced Encrypting
in Bethesda.

06:17.938 --> 06:22.067
Five years, you'll get
your first annual trip to Texas.

06:22.150 --> 06:27.572
You got a wife by then,
.5 kids, 200K a year,

06:27.614 --> 06:30.115
and that's it --
that's the whole show.

06:30.199 --> 06:31.617
Then you're dead.

06:31.659 --> 06:35.913
And it all started because
of one nasty little martini.

06:40.083 --> 06:41.709
So you're a recruiter.

06:41.793 --> 06:44.087
That I am.

06:51.802 --> 06:53.220
You're kidding.

06:53.303 --> 06:57.556
Applications for the CIA
are up tenfold.

06:57.640 --> 06:58.767
Wow.

06:58.809 --> 07:00.310
Would I have to kill anyone?

07:01.520 --> 07:03.105
Would you like to?

07:03.188 --> 07:04.982
Beer man -- Heineken?

07:05.065 --> 07:06.732
Yeah, just a sec.

07:06.816 --> 07:09.485
All I know about the CIA is
that they're a bunch of fat,

07:09.568 --> 07:11.904
old white guys who fell asleep
when we needed them most.

07:11.988 --> 07:14.572
Oh, well, like I said,
you don't know shit.

07:14.656 --> 07:15.782
I know what I know.

07:15.865 --> 07:17.701
-Nice meeting you, James.
-You too.

07:17.784 --> 07:20.578
Way I figure, you'll probably
go in the oil business...

07:20.620 --> 07:22.414
Iike your daddy.

07:31.714 --> 07:32.797
Hey!

07:32.880 --> 07:34.215
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

07:36.342 --> 07:38.594
Did you know my father?

07:41.431 --> 07:45.101
James, I have recruited
and trained and served

07:45.184 --> 07:47.687
with the best
our country has to offer

07:47.729 --> 07:49.480
for over a quarter
of a century.

07:49.522 --> 07:52.149
I am a scary judge of talent.

07:52.232 --> 07:54.234
It's my gift.

07:54.318 --> 07:56.862
I am recruiting you,
Mr. Clayton.

07:56.945 --> 08:00.364
In case you haven't noticed,
I'm not exactly CIA material.

08:00.448 --> 08:02.825
You have any idea
what ClA material is?

08:02.908 --> 08:03.951
It's not me.

08:04.035 --> 08:05.661
No? Well, I don't know.

08:05.745 --> 08:09.248
You graduated
top of your class at M.I.T.,

08:09.332 --> 08:11.458
majored in nonlinear
cryptography,

08:11.541 --> 08:14.377
scored off the charts in your
undergrad psych profile test.

08:14.419 --> 08:15.545
Those are confidential.

08:15.629 --> 08:17.505
Yeah, right.

08:17.589 --> 08:21.508
You're agile,
athletic, and...

08:21.592 --> 08:23.510
And what?

08:23.594 --> 08:28.307
You grew up overseas --
Uzbekistan, Brunei...

08:28.390 --> 08:29.683
Venezuela.

08:29.767 --> 08:31.518
Yeah, my father worked
for Shell awhile.

08:31.560 --> 08:34.563
Your father died in 1990...

08:34.605 --> 08:38.357
in a plane crash in Peru.

08:38.399 --> 08:39.942
What's your point?

08:41.027 --> 08:42.153
What's my point?

08:42.236 --> 08:44.405
What the hell you think
my point is?

08:46.448 --> 08:49.326
My name is Walter Burke.

08:49.409 --> 08:52.162
My number's
on the sports page.

08:52.245 --> 08:53.538
Give me a call.

08:53.622 --> 08:56.248
I'll be here
till noon tomorrow.

09:44.251 --> 09:45.919
Very dramatic, James.

09:46.003 --> 09:48.046
I want to talk.
Can we talk?

09:48.130 --> 09:49.381
Yeah.

09:49.464 --> 09:50.923
Where are you?

09:50.965 --> 09:54.218
Well, you know the phone booth
you're calling from?

09:54.260 --> 09:55.678
Yeah.

09:55.761 --> 09:57.431
Turn around.

10:05.229 --> 10:06.606
As you like it.

10:08.691 --> 10:10.483
You're pretty confident.

10:10.525 --> 10:12.235
Well...

10:12.319 --> 10:14.029
Tell me about my father.

10:16.156 --> 10:18.073
You already know, don't you?

10:18.157 --> 10:20.993
I mean, that's why
you're sitting here.

10:21.076 --> 10:23.787
You want answers,
you're in the wrong car, kid.

10:23.871 --> 10:25.956
I only have secrets.

10:26.040 --> 10:28.583
You can't trust
your best friends,

10:28.666 --> 10:30.001
your five senses,

10:30.043 --> 10:32.962
only the little voice
inside you

10:33.046 --> 10:36.257
most civilians
don't even hear --

10:36.299 --> 10:38.008
Iisten to that.

10:39.426 --> 10:41.471
Trust yourself.

10:41.512 --> 10:44.015
I think that's what
your father would have said.

10:46.099 --> 10:48.268
Trust yourself, James.

11:36.312 --> 11:37.230
Can I help you, sir?

11:37.313 --> 11:38.690
James Clayton --
I'm here for an interview.

11:38.773 --> 11:40.483
Just pull in there,
check in with security.

11:40.566 --> 11:41.733
Thank you.

11:50.408 --> 11:51.784
Hey, my name is James Clayton.

11:51.867 --> 11:54.453
I'm here to see Walter Burke.
He's expecting me.

11:54.537 --> 11:57.164
You can wait for him over there.
I'll page him for you.

12:11.303 --> 12:12.679
James.

12:12.762 --> 12:14.097
Hey.

12:15.307 --> 12:19.143
Rule number one --
don't get caught.

12:19.226 --> 12:21.520
Those were good officers.

12:21.604 --> 12:23.105
Good friends.

12:25.524 --> 12:27.191
So, you ready to get started?

12:27.233 --> 12:28.901
Sure.

12:52.465 --> 12:56.302
Have six pull in tight
on F-4.

12:56.344 --> 12:59.055
All right,
now give me some angles,

12:59.138 --> 13:01.807
both tests...both tests.

13:01.891 --> 13:02.975
Tighter.

13:04.225 --> 13:07.187
It's a carbon copy.

13:07.228 --> 13:09.606
F-4 -- yank him.

13:13.442 --> 13:14.985
You've been caught
cheating, pal.

13:15.027 --> 13:16.820
Please leave.

13:17.905 --> 13:19.907
Still got the eyes, Walter.

13:19.990 --> 13:20.991
What's that story,

13:21.075 --> 13:23.660
you saw some old woman
pushing a baby carriage?

13:23.743 --> 13:27.330
And Walter sees the carriage is
riding a little low, so bam!

13:27.413 --> 13:29.374
No questions, blows grandma
right out of her shoes.

13:29.457 --> 13:30.583
Turned out she was Hamas,

13:30.667 --> 13:32.793
and the whole thing was
stuffed with explosives.

13:32.876 --> 13:34.586
She wasn't Hamas,
she was Abu Nidal.

13:34.670 --> 13:36.129
Abu Nidal, that's right.

13:36.171 --> 13:39.258
These war stories --
you just love them, don't you?

13:49.059 --> 13:51.519
Uh, D-4 --

13:51.602 --> 13:54.313
tell him to forget the chick
and finish the test.

13:59.401 --> 14:02.862
Burke says, "Forget the chick
and finish the test."

14:06.533 --> 14:08.325
How do upsetting problems

14:08.409 --> 14:09.493
generally make you feel?

14:09.577 --> 14:10.494
Upset.

14:10.578 --> 14:12.329
And when you get angry,

14:12.371 --> 14:14.540
do you have trouble
staying in control?

14:14.582 --> 14:15.833
Sure.

14:15.916 --> 14:17.792
How do you typically
deal with failure?

14:17.875 --> 14:19.168
Badly.

14:19.210 --> 14:20.920
Have you ever been deliberately
cruel to an animal?

14:21.004 --> 14:22.630
Yes.

14:22.714 --> 14:23.965
Please, elaborate.

14:24.048 --> 14:27.135
For Christmas, I tied wool
reindeer horns to my dog's head.

14:27.218 --> 14:30.346
Would you consider yourself

14:30.430 --> 14:34.183
subjectively firm
or objectively flexible?

14:35.267 --> 14:37.394
Metaphysically wrinkle-free.

14:37.477 --> 14:39.730
Quickly -- would you rather
ride on a train,

14:39.813 --> 14:42.190
dance in the rain,
or feel no pain?

14:52.867 --> 14:54.910
Feel no pain.

14:54.993 --> 14:59.247
I know I said the rain-dancing
thing, but...feel no pain.

15:00.624 --> 15:02.250
Thank you.

15:11.927 --> 15:13.969
God, I hate this.

15:14.053 --> 15:15.721
Hey.

15:15.804 --> 15:16.847
Hi.

15:16.931 --> 15:18.349
I'm James.

15:19.558 --> 15:21.018
Layla.

15:21.060 --> 15:22.894
Like the song.

15:24.520 --> 15:25.855
Yeah.

15:25.897 --> 15:27.649
That's a big coffee.

15:27.732 --> 15:30.235
I'm a big girl.

15:30.318 --> 15:31.526
Sure.

15:31.610 --> 15:33.403
Is your name James Clayton?

15:33.445 --> 15:36.156
James Douglas Clayton.

15:36.240 --> 15:38.575
Just a yes-or-no answer.

15:38.617 --> 15:41.244
Is your name James Clayton?

15:41.285 --> 15:42.536
Yes.

15:42.620 --> 15:47.208
You were born
October 21, 1976?

15:47.291 --> 15:48.875
Yes.

15:48.959 --> 15:51.711
Have you ever worked for
any foreign governments?

15:51.753 --> 15:52.796
No.

15:52.879 --> 15:55.758
Have you taken tranquilizers
today?

15:55.841 --> 15:57.593
No.

16:13.566 --> 16:14.775
Miami.

16:16.693 --> 16:17.735
Mind if I sit here?

16:17.819 --> 16:18.903
Sure.

16:21.739 --> 16:23.575
Hey.
Ronnie Gibson from D.C.

16:23.658 --> 16:25.201
James Clayton from all over.

16:25.285 --> 16:26.910
Nice to meet you.

16:26.952 --> 16:27.911
You too.

16:32.374 --> 16:35.126
You got any idea what those two
are speaking over there?

16:35.209 --> 16:37.044
I think it's Farsi.

16:37.128 --> 16:39.506
Oh, yeah. Yeah, Farsi.

17:27.467 --> 17:28.635
Clear!

18:17.011 --> 18:19.639
Uh, what are you doing?

18:19.681 --> 18:21.391
Nothing.

18:21.474 --> 18:22.433
What?

18:22.475 --> 18:24.769
Some of these chairs
are wired.

18:24.851 --> 18:26.770
They catch you drifting
during this,

18:26.853 --> 18:28.105
10,000 volts up your ass.

18:28.188 --> 18:29.439
Bullshit.

18:29.481 --> 18:31.358
All right.

18:31.400 --> 18:33.110
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

18:33.193 --> 18:35.111
Ladies and gentlemen,
my name is Dennis Slayne.

18:35.194 --> 18:37.280
I'm assistant director
of operations at Langley,

18:37.363 --> 18:39.115
and I would like
to welcome you here

18:39.156 --> 18:40.950
to the CIA Special
Training Facility,

18:40.992 --> 18:44.244
affectionately known
as "the farm."

18:44.327 --> 18:45.370
Now let me introduce to you

18:45.453 --> 18:47.122
your senior instructor,
Mr. Walter Burke.

18:47.163 --> 18:48.373
Morning.

18:48.456 --> 18:49.833
Morning.

18:52.544 --> 18:54.546
So, why are you here?

18:54.629 --> 18:56.965
Why are you here?

18:59.092 --> 19:01.219
It ain't the money.

19:01.261 --> 19:05.556
A GS-15 pay grade officer,
yours truly --

19:05.598 --> 19:09.894
I rake in about, what,
75 grand a year?

19:09.935 --> 19:14.397
You can't buy
a decent sports car for that.

19:14.439 --> 19:16.065
It ain't sex.

19:16.149 --> 19:19.152
Hey, being here
won't get you laid.

19:19.235 --> 19:20.819
Oh, you're
a dental hygienist?

19:20.903 --> 19:25.282
I'm a member of the CIA,
Moscow Station chief.

19:25.365 --> 19:27.326
-Hello?!

19:27.409 --> 19:29.827
What about fame?

19:29.911 --> 19:33.080
Our failures are known.

19:33.164 --> 19:37.836
Our successes...are not.

19:37.878 --> 19:39.587
That's the company motto.

19:39.670 --> 19:42.256
You save the world,

19:42.340 --> 19:46.135
they send you to some
dusty basement at Langley,

19:46.177 --> 19:48.136
give you a little lemonade
and cookies,

19:48.178 --> 19:49.679
and show you your medal.

19:49.763 --> 19:51.306
You don't even get
to take it home.

19:51.389 --> 19:54.226
So it ain't money,
it ain't sex, it ain't fame.

19:54.309 --> 19:55.560
What is it?

19:55.644 --> 19:59.772
I say we are all here
in this room

19:59.855 --> 20:03.234
because we believe.

20:03.317 --> 20:07.111
We believe in good and evil,

20:07.153 --> 20:08.738
and we choose good.

20:08.821 --> 20:11.533
We believe in right and wrong,

20:11.616 --> 20:13.952
and we choose right.

20:14.035 --> 20:16.662
Our cause is just.

20:16.745 --> 20:21.833
Our enemies...everywhere.

20:21.918 --> 20:24.503
They're all around us.

20:24.586 --> 20:26.547
Some scary stuff out there.

20:26.630 --> 20:30.801
Which brings us here...
to the farm.

20:30.884 --> 20:35.221
You have all just stepped
through the looking glass.

20:35.263 --> 20:37.723
What you see, what you hear --

20:37.807 --> 20:41.185
nothing is what it seems.

20:42.894 --> 20:45.397
Indistinct conversations

20:48.608 --> 20:51.069
Mr. Burke?

20:51.152 --> 20:52.653
Hey.

20:52.736 --> 20:56.740
I was just, uh...I was hoping
maybe I could buy you a beer

20:56.824 --> 20:58.117
and we could talk.

20:58.200 --> 21:00.578
I have so many questions
about my dad.

21:00.661 --> 21:02.328
You're making a mistake, son.

21:02.412 --> 21:04.372
Let me remedy it.

21:04.414 --> 21:06.959
I was on semicongenial terms
with you

21:07.001 --> 21:09.503
during your recruitment
for that reason --

21:09.587 --> 21:10.795
I was recruiting you.

21:10.879 --> 21:12.338
I'm not your friend.

21:12.422 --> 21:14.674
I'm not your ally.

21:16.551 --> 21:20.262
I'm your instructor --
period.

21:20.345 --> 21:22.264
That enough talk?

21:33.858 --> 21:36.319
Good morning. It's 0600.

21:36.402 --> 21:39.946
All CTs report
to Common Area, 15 minutes.

21:41.698 --> 21:42.866
Is everybody ready?

21:46.912 --> 21:47.828
Morning.

21:47.912 --> 21:49.205
-Let's go.

21:49.288 --> 21:51.374
Let's go!

21:53.168 --> 21:55.587
Over the next few months,

21:55.670 --> 21:58.297
we're gonna teach you
how to deceive,

21:58.380 --> 22:02.384
role-play,
psychologically assess,

22:02.468 --> 22:05.221
sell, exploit.

22:05.262 --> 22:07.263
We're gonna hand you
the tools --

22:07.347 --> 22:08.765
the black arts.

22:08.848 --> 22:12.393
Not witchcraft --
trade craft...

22:12.477 --> 22:14.270
Ready! Fire!

22:15.979 --> 22:19.107
...disguise, surveil, detect.

22:19.191 --> 22:22.611
You will be able to kill
with a variety of weapons...

22:22.694 --> 22:24.737
-or none at all.

22:26.322 --> 22:29.659
You will night-parachute,
rappel from choppers,

22:29.700 --> 22:31.994
Iearn dry and wet demolition,

22:32.078 --> 22:35.664
Iearn tactical, high-speed
emergency driving.

22:35.747 --> 22:36.958
You will become...

22:37.041 --> 22:40.294
Bond -- James Bond.

22:40.378 --> 22:41.838
Thank you, Mr. Clayton.

22:41.921 --> 22:44.631
You're already role-playing.
That's good.

22:44.714 --> 22:46.299
You're ahead of all of us.

22:46.383 --> 22:49.636
Let's start with Clayton.
Why don't you take...Zack?

22:53.472 --> 22:54.849
Aah!

22:54.932 --> 22:56.433
Nice move.

22:56.517 --> 22:58.853
Where the hell did
you learn how to do that?

22:58.894 --> 23:01.604
Metro Dade Police Academy.

23:01.688 --> 23:03.690
Are you a senior
instructor at the farm?

23:03.773 --> 23:04.858
-Yes.

23:04.899 --> 23:06.151
True.

23:06.234 --> 23:08.153
Okay, if you look
at the screens,

23:08.236 --> 23:10.445
you'll see his pulse is even,

23:10.529 --> 23:12.739
respiration normal,

23:12.823 --> 23:15.367
pupils undilated --
signs of the truth.

23:15.450 --> 23:17.995
Come on, rough me up.
Let's go! Rough me up!

23:18.078 --> 23:20.371
Have you ever worn
women's clothing?

23:21.540 --> 23:22.791
Who said that?

23:22.833 --> 23:23.834
Yes.

23:23.876 --> 23:25.794
-True.

23:27.087 --> 23:30.673
Were you, uh,
ever stationed in Peru?

23:30.756 --> 23:32.008
Yes.

23:32.091 --> 23:33.801
True.

23:33.885 --> 23:36.470
Is your name Walter Burke?

23:36.554 --> 23:38.680
