51:45.305 --> 51:46.265
Bullshit.

51:46.306 --> 51:48.891
The washout was faked.

51:48.975 --> 51:50.476
You're the NOC.

51:50.560 --> 51:53.104
I told you I was
a scary judge of talent.

51:55.690 --> 51:57.107
Why me?

51:58.525 --> 52:00.026
Get in here.

52:03.321 --> 52:04.906
I don't believe this.

52:07.992 --> 52:09.368
More farm mind games.

52:09.410 --> 52:11.203
Nothing is what it seems,
na na na.

52:11.287 --> 52:13.247
No, no, no, no.
School's out.

52:13.289 --> 52:16.958
Open that, uh,
glove compartment.

52:17.041 --> 52:18.334
Go ahead.

52:22.798 --> 52:24.674
Find out why you.

52:37.185 --> 52:38.937
That's why you.

52:39.021 --> 52:40.147
Layla? Wh--

52:40.230 --> 52:42.190
Layla Moore --

52:42.232 --> 52:45.109
raised from the age of 3
by Tom and Susan Moore

52:45.192 --> 52:47.111
of Worcester, Mass.

52:47.194 --> 52:50.823
However, her real last name
isn't Moore -- it's Nasari.

52:50.865 --> 52:53.658
Birth mother is Algerian,
father's French.

52:53.742 --> 52:55.202
It's all there --

52:55.285 --> 53:00.749
secret bank accounts,
phony records, fake passports.

53:00.831 --> 53:02.791
Layla's a sleeper.

53:02.875 --> 53:05.586
She's a mole, James.

53:08.548 --> 53:10.341
I don't believe it.
This is crazy.

53:10.424 --> 53:12.593
How the hell
did she get into the farm --

53:12.676 --> 53:14.220
We wanted her in.

53:14.261 --> 53:17.139
We want her to burrow in
as deep as she can,

53:17.181 --> 53:19.641
because then, she'll lead us
to her handlers.

53:19.724 --> 53:21.267
We know exactly
what she wants.

53:21.351 --> 53:24.938
It's who she's giving it to --
that's what we need to know.

53:24.979 --> 53:27.982
Layla's gonna take us
right up the food chain.

53:28.066 --> 53:29.691
I won't do it.

53:29.775 --> 53:31.109
You won't do it?

53:31.193 --> 53:34.321
James...

53:34.404 --> 53:37.949
why do you think I came
to Cambridge to recruit you?

53:38.032 --> 53:40.117
Nobody's chasing CTs anymore.

53:40.201 --> 53:42.453
I mean, our applications
are through the roof.

53:42.537 --> 53:45.957
We needed you...James.

53:46.040 --> 53:47.415
No accidents.

53:47.457 --> 53:49.876
You and Layla were matched.

53:49.960 --> 53:51.712
She's an orphan.

53:51.796 --> 53:54.048
You're a young man
searching for a father.

53:54.131 --> 53:56.925
You're both highly motivated,
you're both highly independent.

53:57.008 --> 53:59.511
You even look good together.

54:01.221 --> 54:03.848
We paired you at the farm, son.

54:03.932 --> 54:06.308
We paired you, remember?

54:06.350 --> 54:08.394
The Blue Ridge barhop?

54:08.477 --> 54:10.938
The lie detector session?

54:11.021 --> 54:13.065
The choke point test?

54:13.148 --> 54:15.692
And it worked, didn't it?

54:15.775 --> 54:17.610
She trusts you.

54:17.694 --> 54:19.112
Loves you, maybe.

54:19.195 --> 54:22.532
And you're gonna take
that trust and that love

54:22.574 --> 54:25.284
and you're gonna use it to
find out who she's working for.

54:29.788 --> 54:31.248
James...

54:33.875 --> 54:37.421
My first posting was
in ltaly -- Trieste.

54:37.504 --> 54:40.632
A physics conference
met there every summer.

54:40.716 --> 54:44.468
So I meet this local girl --
beautiful, sweet.

54:44.552 --> 54:48.180
She's working for the Russian
group as a secretary.

54:48.264 --> 54:51.808
Anyway, I did my job.
I worked her. I turned her.

54:51.892 --> 54:54.394
Pretty soon, she's giving me
everything, you know --

54:54.477 --> 54:57.397
I mean,
really high-grade stuff --

54:57.480 --> 55:00.441
and, uh, I'm a hero.

55:00.524 --> 55:03.694
But I'm still a kid, two years,
fresh out of Ocala, Florida.

55:03.777 --> 55:06.530
I got this perfect ltalian girl,
and she's crazy for me,

55:06.572 --> 55:08.073
and we're falling in love.

55:08.157 --> 55:11.868
I knew the Russians were
getting close to her.

55:11.951 --> 55:14.913
I knew she was
in jeopardy, but...

55:14.996 --> 55:16.789
material was valuable.

55:18.041 --> 55:19.875
I could've warned her.

55:21.961 --> 55:23.922
I could've saved her.

55:25.298 --> 55:28.008
But the information
was more important.

55:29.343 --> 55:31.053
You understand?

55:31.136 --> 55:35.641
The information was more
important than she was...

55:35.724 --> 55:38.809
more important than I was.

55:42.522 --> 55:44.690
It is what we do.

55:49.986 --> 55:51.446
I need to think about it.

55:51.488 --> 55:53.990
Oh, come on.
"Think about it."

55:55.158 --> 55:57.409
You got 24 hours.

56:15.260 --> 56:16.219
Burke here.

56:16.261 --> 56:18.054
Okay.

56:18.054 --> 56:19.264
I'll do it.

56:21.349 --> 56:22.684
Iwo Jima Memorial --

56:22.767 --> 56:26.270
this is where you tell me
about duty and sacrifice?

56:26.353 --> 56:28.313
No, this is where I have
my breakfast burrito.

56:32.191 --> 56:34.569
Volente Brothers.

56:34.652 --> 56:36.863
They're the best.

56:36.946 --> 56:37.864
There you go.

56:37.947 --> 56:39.949
-Gracias,
-Thank you.

56:39.991 --> 56:43.159
Try it. It's heaven.

56:45.245 --> 56:46.371
So, what is she after?

56:46.454 --> 56:49.374
You ever read Kurt Vonnegut?

56:49.457 --> 56:50.418
Yeah.

56:50.459 --> 56:52.961
-You read "Cat's Cradle"?
-Nah.

56:53.044 --> 56:57.382
Well, in that book,
the world ends

56:57.465 --> 57:01.051
because in a chip of ice,
a molecule is discovered

57:01.093 --> 57:05.973
that can turn all the water
it touches into ice.

57:06.056 --> 57:08.434
Since all water
is interconnected --

57:08.517 --> 57:11.477
that is, pond to stream,
stream to river,

57:11.561 --> 57:14.314
river to lake,
lake to ocean --

57:14.397 --> 57:17.025
the entire world freezes
and dies,

57:17.108 --> 57:22.487
and that seed molecule
is called lce 9.

57:22.529 --> 57:24.448
Ice 9.

57:24.489 --> 57:27.950
Langley has invented
a computer virus

57:28.034 --> 57:32.163
that can plug into
any electrical receptacle --

57:32.246 --> 57:36.084
that is, the wall outlet
in your apartment --

57:36.168 --> 57:37.752
using existing wiring

57:37.835 --> 57:40.463
to spread right through
the entire national grid.

57:40.546 --> 57:43.007
No firewalls, no protection.

57:43.090 --> 57:44.217
Jesus.

57:44.300 --> 57:45.301
That's it.

57:46.384 --> 57:47.886
Our national defense,

57:47.969 --> 57:51.181
our national survival
depends on electronics.

57:51.264 --> 57:52.766
You take that away...

57:52.849 --> 57:55.559
we're back in the Stone Age
with our enemies.

57:57.561 --> 57:59.605
This was good.

57:59.688 --> 58:01.232
Can I make it?

58:03.776 --> 58:05.944
Oh! So close.

58:11.407 --> 58:13.492
You're going to Langley.

58:14.868 --> 58:19.707
Your cover story is that
you washed out of the farm,

58:19.791 --> 58:21.125
but we love you --

58:21.167 --> 58:23.126
you're a good boy,
a patriot --

58:23.210 --> 58:26.922
so we got you a low-level,
low-security gig...

58:26.964 --> 58:31.051
but your real assignment
is to get close to Layla

58:31.134 --> 58:33.594
and to stay close to her.

58:33.678 --> 58:36.556
Find out who she's talking to.

59:00.994 --> 59:02.745
Layla requested Cryptography,

59:02.829 --> 59:03.789
so we gave it to her.

59:03.873 --> 59:06.542
She's working at the Directorate
of Science and Technology

59:06.625 --> 59:07.543
in Langley.

59:07.626 --> 59:09.544
Well, if she's
a new employee in Langley,

59:09.627 --> 59:11.379
isn't surveillance on her
24/7?

59:11.462 --> 59:13.381
They've got to find out
what she's up to.

59:13.464 --> 59:16.050
Langley's security is
all about entry and exit --

59:16.134 --> 59:17.218
going in, going out.

59:17.302 --> 59:18.886
-You are scoped, taped...
-Morning.

59:18.927 --> 59:20.888
...tagged like no other
place on Earth,

59:20.929 --> 59:22.556
but once you're on the inside,

59:22.598 --> 59:24.475
the assumption is
you belong there.

59:24.558 --> 59:26.393
-Langley's too big to watch.

59:26.435 --> 59:28.311
We're a city, and as such,

59:28.394 --> 59:30.855
we are vulnerable
to betrayal from within,

59:30.938 --> 59:32.690
always have been --
Ames, Nickelson, Howard.

59:32.773 --> 59:34.233
So what have you got me doing?

59:34.275 --> 59:35.443
We've given you

59:35.526 --> 59:37.527
a low-level data-processing
position

59:37.611 --> 59:39.779
in the information
management center --

59:39.863 --> 59:42.657
not uncommon for CTs
who don't graduate the farm.

59:42.699 --> 59:43.700
You'll love it.

59:43.742 --> 59:45.868
-Mr. Clayton?
-Hey.

59:45.951 --> 59:47.912
-Rob Stevens, your supervisor.
-Nice to meet you.

59:47.953 --> 59:49.623
-Welcome to CIA.
-Thank you.

59:53.210 --> 59:55.878
The building we're going into
is totally secure.

59:55.961 --> 59:58.756
No radio-wave transmissions
in or out.

59:58.839 --> 01:00:02.301
Electronic devices --
computers, telephones --

01:00:02.384 --> 01:00:04.594
even your voice
create vibrations

01:00:04.636 --> 01:00:06.596
that a sophisticated laser
pointer in the building

01:00:06.679 --> 01:00:08.890
-can read and translate.

01:00:12.935 --> 01:00:15.646
I'll tell you, this card won't
get you into the good stuff,

01:00:15.729 --> 01:00:18.232
but that little logo
definitely gets you laid.

01:00:18.273 --> 01:00:20.859
Republican girls -- hot.

01:00:22.235 --> 01:00:23.903
Here we go. This is you.

01:00:25.988 --> 01:00:28.491
The manual's
pretty self-explanatory.

01:00:28.574 --> 01:00:31.326
Log in as much data as you can
without getting carpal tunnel.

01:00:31.368 --> 01:00:32.744
Any questions, I'm 1229.

01:00:32.786 --> 01:00:33.746
Thank you.

01:00:43.255 --> 01:00:44.381
Thank you.

01:00:44.464 --> 01:00:46.550
I'll see you over there.

01:00:47.926 --> 01:00:49.010
James.

01:00:49.094 --> 01:00:51.095
Layla. Hey.

01:00:51.178 --> 01:00:54.014
What ar--
oh, you're here?

01:00:54.098 --> 01:00:55.683
Yep. Data entry.

01:00:55.766 --> 01:00:57.601
Not exactly
what I'd imagined, but...

01:00:58.685 --> 01:01:01.813
After you left...
we missed you at the farm.

01:01:01.896 --> 01:01:03.982
Yeah.

01:01:04.065 --> 01:01:06.109
Look, I'm late, so...

01:01:06.192 --> 01:01:08.360
Oh, right. Okay.

01:01:08.443 --> 01:01:10.404
It's good to see you.

01:01:10.445 --> 01:01:12.573
Yeah. You too.

01:01:12.656 --> 01:01:13.824
Take care.

01:01:18.912 --> 01:01:20.706
-Hi, Frank.
-Hey, how's it going?

01:01:20.747 --> 01:01:21.748
Good.

01:01:26.544 --> 01:01:27.962
